 | A-065 | Verified PAN/Aadhaar corrections use `POST /api/v1/members/{id}/reverification/` with current `version`, at least one identity value, and a reason. The action atomically resets member KYC to pending; the last member creator/editor cannot verify the resulting member KYC document. | M02-FR-012 requires an approved change request and the slice requires a reverification path, but API §13 names no approval-case resource or endpoint. A dedicated reasoned transition avoids silently overloading PATCH; maker-checker is enforced at the existing KYC verification boundary without inventing an approval authority. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M02-FR-012; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §13; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §18/§25.1; `docs/slices/006Y-member-create-update-and-identity-governance.md` | 006Y and future governance confirmation | High | Yes | 2026-07-12 | If governance defines a formal identity-change approval case or separate reverification permission, version this endpoint and preserve masked history/audit, optimistic locking, and verifier separation. |
 | A-066 | Witness correction is read-only in 006Y2 after capture because the delivered 004E/004E2 contract exposes only application-scoped GET/POST and names no editable fields, PATCH endpoint, version rule, update permission, or audit event. | Implementing a client-only edit or guessing a write contract would invent governance behavior; 006Y2 explicitly makes backend contract changes out of scope and requires mismatches to be recorded. | `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S09; `docs/source/api-contracts.md`; `docs/slices/004E-witness-shareholder-validation.md`; `docs/slices/004E2-witness-evidence-snapshot-and-input-hardening.md`; `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` | 006Y2 and a future witness-correction contract slice | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-12 | Add edit only after the backend projects a resource action and defines optimistic update, permitted fields, immutable evidence behavior, and metadata-only audit evidence. |
 | A-067 | The member registration/edit surface is isolated in `MemberGovernanceForm` while using only the existing card, field, alert, button, grid, colour, spacing, and typography classes. | Registration and reasoned identity correction have shared state/payload/error behavior and no existing component can express that form without duplicating it across Directory and Profile; the binding design rules require recording an absolutely-required new component. | `docs/working/FRONTEND_DESIGN_RULES.md`; existing `MemberDirectory.tsx` and `MemberProfile.tsx` patterns | 006Y2 | Low | No | 2026-07-12 | This is a composition boundary, not a new visual system; do not add bespoke styles or generalize it beyond governed member mutations. |
+| A-068 | `members.member.identity_change.approve` is seeded as a dedicated high-risk permission with no default role assignment; administrators must explicitly grant it to the checker role selected by governance. | M02-FR-012 requires approval and 006Y3 forbids a hard-coded approver role, while the source permission catalogue does not assign a named identity-change checker. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M02-FR-012; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.2, §17-§18; `docs/slices/006Y3-member-registry-and-identity-change-approval-closure.md` | 006Y3 | High | Yes | 2026-07-12 | The requester must also differ from the approver; add a default role grant only when governance names that role. |
